          "slidetitle": "Identifying Bias in Eligibility Systems",
          "subtitle": "Where Unfair Patterns Often Take Root",
          "slidecontent": "• Training data that reflects historical inequalities in benefit access\n• Proxy variables (like postcode or employment type) that indirectly encode protected characteristics\n• Opaque scoring models with no clear audit trail\n• Inconsistent data quality across different demographic groups\n• Feedback loops that reinforce past denial patterns over time\n• Human-designed rules that embed existing systemic disadvantage"
