          "number": 5,
          "slidetitle": "Challenging Bias in AI Systems",
          "subtitle": "Recognising and Addressing Systemic Unfairness",
          "slidecontent": "• AI systems trained on historical data can inherit and replicate past discrimination in benefit decisions\n• Biased outputs often appear neutral because they are wrapped in technical language\n• Certain groups (older applicants, ethnic minorities, disabled people) face higher rates of unfair rejection\n• Bias is not always intentional\n• Regular auditing of AI decisions helps surface patterns of unequal treatment before they cause widespread harm\n• Frontline staff need clear routes to flag and escalate suspected bias in automated eligibility tools"
